{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"u0l1tk4o1kysx28cxpdr2vp","title":"Design","desc":"","updated":1654588386223,"created":1654540333207,"custom":{},"fname":"cs.webdev.frontend.language.js.jsframework.react.state-management.types-of-application-state.client-state.design","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"d2860b171580227ca8453e61cf9593f9","links":[],"anchors":{},"children":["kwor9uu68paz3kuy4rd5hzr","3k3jut4tw2brwahs3j28qqz","qp0uwf7dogj9emc6zjq0mh5","r8ngopnb8lhaywyiylmo4ni","jhi4jwkh04kwzd3bp25wofh","1ipohwlx1rg886x4j5hoqdk"],"parent":"zp3wf6ep0tl5u2qkfqocsrk","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"design\">Design<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#design\"></a></h1>\n<p>Whenever we are designing any kind of UI state management system, we must keep in mind to <strong>keep the state as low as possible</strong>.</p>\n<p>The few ways we can design a Client state management system are the following:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Local state using <code>useState</code> hooks.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Lifting the state and then passing down the <code>props</code> via <code>prop</code> drilling.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Global states using <code>contexts</code>.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>When we are dealing with global states, we can also use Redux, MobX etc.</p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Children</strong>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/Personal-Knowledge-Vault/notes/kwor9uu68paz3kuy4rd5hzr\">Colocating the State</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/Personal-Knowledge-Vault/notes/3k3jut4tw2brwahs3j28qqz\">Composition</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/Personal-Knowledge-Vault/notes/qp0uwf7dogj9emc6zjq0mh5\">Global State</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/Personal-Knowledge-Vault/notes/r8ngopnb8lhaywyiylmo4ni\">Local State</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/Personal-Knowledge-Vault/notes/jhi4jwkh04kwzd3bp25wofh\">Performance</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/Personal-Knowledge-Vault/notes/1ipohwlx1rg886x4j5hoqdk\">Prop Drilling</a></li>\n</ol>","noteIndex":{"id":"2rzu5qtc4erc8gkfiteeysj","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":165545739